<ext_description linkend="Shield_arm.Shield"><p>
A <b>Shield</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Physical_unit_design_view:arm:Physical_unit_design_view_arm.Assembly_component"/> included 
for suppression of unwanted electromagnetic coupling among components.
An  <express_ref linkend="Physical_unit_design_view:arm:Physical_unit_design_view_arm.Assembly_component"/> included in the assembly for other purposes might also serve as a <b>Shield</b>, and in that case the other type would be specified as well for that instance.

</p><example number="1">
A <express_ref linkend="Layered_interconnect_module_design:arm:Layered_interconnect_module_design_arm.Via"/> may be a <b>Shield</b>. More than one shield may shield the same <b>shielded_item</b> for the same purpose.
</example>
<example number="2">
Figure <express_ref linkend="shield"/> illustrates a detail of a layout drawing that shows a shielded trace (carrying a critical signal) on the several layers it traverses in the design.
</example>
<figure id="shield"><title>Shield</title><img src="shield.gif"/></figure>
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Shield_arm.Shield.shielded_item">
the <b>shielded_item</b> specifies either an <express_ref linkend="Physical_unit_design_view:arm:Physical_unit_design_view_arm.Assembly_component"/>, a <express_ref linkend="Component_feature:arm:Component_feature_arm.Component_feature"/>, or a <express_ref linkend="Functional_design_elaboration:arm:Functional_design_elaboration_arm.Physical_connectivity_definition"/> as the shieldable item for a <b>Shield</b>.
There shall be one or more  <express_ref linkend="Physical_unit_design_view:arm:Physical_unit_design_view_arm.Assembly_component"/>,  <express_ref linkend="Component_feature:arm:Component_feature_arm.Component_feature"/>, or  <express_ref linkend="Functional_design_elaboration:arm:Functional_design_elaboration_arm.Physical_connectivity_definition"/> for a <b>Shield</b>.
</ext_description>
</ext_descriptions>
